---
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import CommonMetaTags from "../components/CommonMetaTags.astro";
import CommonBanner from "../components/CommonBanner.astro";
import Gallery from "../components/Gallery.astro";

import { mathrusangamList } from "../data/mathrusangamData.js";
import PeopleTable from "../components/PeopleTable.astro";

const pageUrl = "https://stjosephchurchairoli.in/mathrusangam/";
const pageTitle = "Mathrusangam - St. Joseph's Church, Airoli";

const cmsUrl =
  "https://ap-south-1.cdn.hygraph.com/content/cleslmwlh2c5j01ujd6j7gzuf/master?query=query%20Assets%20%7B%0A%20%20galleries(orderBy%3A%20year_DESC%2C%20where%3A%20%7Btags%3A%20Mathrusangam%7D)%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20year%0A%20%20%20%20tags%0A%20%20%20%20imageFile%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20url%0A%20%20%20%20%7D%0A%20%20%20%20caption%0A%20%20%7D%0A%7D%0A&operationName=Assets";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="no-js">
  <head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <!-- Facebook Meta Tags -->
    <meta property="og:url" content={pageUrl} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={pageTitle} />

    <!-- Twitter Meta Tags -->
    <meta property="twitter:url" content={pageUrl} />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={pageTitle} />

    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <CommonMetaTags />
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />
    <CommonBanner title="Mathrusangam" />

    <section class="course-details-area pt-10 pb-40">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-12 left-contents">
            <div class="jq-tab-wrapper" id="horizontalTab">
              <div class="jq-tab-menu">
                <div class="jq-tab-title active" data-tab="1">About</div>
                <div class="jq-tab-title" data-tab="2">Executives</div>
              </div>
              <div class="jq-tab-content-wrapper">
                <div class="jq-tab-content active" data-tab="1">
                  Since the beginning of the church, Mathrusangam has existed
                  with the primary goal of enlightening Christ via motherhood.
                  Mothers, who are the lights of families, are helped and
                  supported by the members of Mathrusangam. On March 25, 1996,
                  Mar Paul Chittilapilly issued a proclamation establishing
                  Kalyan Mathrusangham, and Msgr. Thomas Thalachira served as
                  the organization's first director.
                  <br />
                  <blockquote class="generic-blockquote">
                    <strong
                      >"Her children rise up and call her blessed; her husband
                      also, and he praises her."
                      <br />
                    </strong>
                    <em><b>Proverbs 31:28</b></em>
                  </blockquote>
                  Currently, Kalyan Mathrusangham (KMS) has over 6500 mothers as
                  members, and they collaborate closely with other organizations
                  at the parish, zonal, and diocese levels. Mathrusangam aims to
                  provide support and encouragement to mothers within the church
                  community. They offer a platform for mothers to connect, share
                  experiences, and uplift one another in their journey of motherhood.
                  <br /><br />
                  Their primary objective is to deepen their faith, provide spiritual
                  guidance, and equip them to be godly mothers and role models. The
                  members of Mathrusangam solely organize the feasts of MotherMary
                  especially 'Mathavinte Vanakkamasam' in the month of May. Additionally,
                  they take part in a variety of diocesan activities like group singing,
                  mime, bible quizzes, etc., which allows them to witness Christ
                  through their deeds.
                  <br /><br />
                  The association recognizes the unique challenges and joys of motherhood
                  and seeks to empower and uplift mothers in their Christian faith
                  and their role as mothers.
                  <br />
                </div>
                <div class="jq-tab-content" data-tab="2">
                  <PeopleTable dataList={mathrusangamList} />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Gallery cmsUrl={cmsUrl} />
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
